# AGENTS.local.md.example

This file is an example for private, machine-specific operator notes.

- Copy this file to `AGENTS.local.md` if you want local deployment guidance that stays out of Git.
- Do not store secrets here.
- Put real secret values in `.env` instead.

Suggested contents:

- deployment hostnames
- SSH usernames
- exact deploy commands for your environment
- post-deploy smoke test notes
- one-off operational caveats for your server

Example:

```md
# AGENTS.local.md

## Local Deploy Notes

- Deploy host: `your-server.example.com`
- Deploy user: `your-user`
- Smoke test after deploy: send a message through port `465` and check journald plus Gmail Inbox delivery.
- If the service is already running, use `sudo systemctl restart smtp2cf`.
```
